# CareFlow AI – Hospital Operations Assistant

This plan outlines the architecture and implementation steps for building the CareFlow AI frontend application, an impressive and modern web app designed to streamline hospital operations.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> The project will be built using Vite with React and Vanilla CSS (no Tailwind, per standard guidelines) to ensure maximum flexibility and a custom premium feel. All state and interactions will be simulated on the client-side to be demo-ready without a backend.
> Do you approve of this technology stack and the plan to initialize the project in `C:\Users\Dell\.gemini\antigravity\scratch\careflow-ai`?

## Open Questions
- Are there specific patient cases or AI responses you'd like hardcoded into the demonstration, or should I generate realistic generic medical data?
- Should the AI Assistant Panel be a side drawer, a floating chat widget, or a dedicated main view? (I plan to implement it as a collapsible side panel alongside the main dashboard).

## Proposed Architecture and Stack
- **Framework:** React 18 via Vite (`create-vite`)
- **Styling:** Vanilla CSS with extensive use of CSS variables for theming (Soft blue, white, light gradients, rounded corners).
- **Icons:** `lucide-react` for clean, modern iconography.
- **Animations:** CSS transitions and keyframes for smooth micro-interactions, toast notifications, and typing effects.
- **State Management:** React Context API / Hooks for managing mocked patient data, AI chat state, and notification toasts.

## Implementation Steps

### 1. Project Initialization
- Scaffold a new React project using Vite in `C:\Users\Dell\.gemini\antigravity\scratch\careflow-ai`.
- Clean up default boilerplate and set up the directory structure (`components`, `styles`, `data`, `hooks`).

### 2. Design System and Theming (`styles/index.css`)
- Define CSS variables for the color palette (soft blues, clean whites, slate text).
- Implement global styles for premium typography (e.g., importing Inter or Outfit from Google Fonts).
- Create utility classes for glassmorphism, soft shadows, and layout grids.

### 3. Core Layout Components
- **Sidebar/Navigation:** Clean vertical navigation.
- **Top Bar:** Search, User Profile, and Quick Stats.
- **Main Layout Grid:** CSS Grid to position the Dashboard and the AI Assistant Panel.

### 4. Feature Implementation
#### Smart Dashboard & Quick Actions
- Develop the "Quick Stats" cards with subtle hover animations.
- Implement the "Quick Actions" panel with action buttons.
- Create the "Patient Management View" table with simulated real-time status updates.

#### AI Assistant Panel
- Build the chat interface component.
- Implement a stateful hook to handle user input.
- Simulate an AI typing effect (streaming response) using `setTimeout`/`setInterval`.

#### Notification System
- Build a Toast Provider and Toast components.
- Hook into the Quick Actions and AI Assistant to trigger "mock" alerts and success messages.

### 5. Data Mocking and Polish
- Populate `data/mockData.js` with realistic patient records, staff schedules, and predefined AI intents.
- Ensure the layout is responsive and looks pristine on both desktop and tablet views.

## Verification Plan
### Automated Tests
- Run `npm run build` to verify the production bundle compiles without errors.
- Run `npm run lint` if applicable to ensure code quality.

### Manual Verification
- Start the Vite development server (`npm run dev`).
- Open a browser subagent or ask the user to view the application in their browser to verify:
  - The aesthetics match the premium, calming medical theme.
  - The AI Assistant correctly simulates a typing response.
  - Toast notifications appear appropriately when quick actions are clicked.
